-- Romanian Leu Gains as U.S. Data Boosts Investors’ Risk Appetite
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-09-25T14:23:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/romanian-leu-gains-as-u-s-data-boosts-investors-risk-appetite.html
The leu strengthened after  home
prices  in the U.S. climbed more than forecast, signaling the
world’s largest economy is showing signs of improvement and
increasing appetite for riskier assets.  The currency gained 0.1 percent to 4.5106 per euro at 5:15
p.m. in Bucharest, recovering from yesterday’s decline, when
it touched the weakest since Aug. 13, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  Yields on the country’s 2018 euro-denominated bond fell
three basis points, or 0.03 percentage point, to 4.828 percent.  The S&P/Case-Shiller index of property values in 20 U.S.
cities increased 1.2 percent from July 2011, the biggest 12-
month advance since August 2010, adding to signs housing will
spur economic growth in the U.S.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
